            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><p>\n  By Katherine Hamilton </p><br/><p>\n  Sherwin-Williams raised its quarterly dividend by 1.3% to 80 cents a share. </p><!-- Article --><p>\n\n  The Cleveland-based paint company last raised its dividend to 79 cents from 71.5 cents in February 2025. </p><p>\n\n  The new payout, equal to $3.20 a year, represents an annual yield of 0.9% based on Tuesday's closing price of $367.94. </p><p>\n\n  Sherwin-Williams plans to pay the dividend on March 13 to shareholders of record as of March 2. </p><br/><p>\n  Write to Katherine Hamilton at katherine.hamilton@wsj.com </p><br/><p>\n  (END) Dow Jones Newswires</p><p>\n\n  02-18-26 1347ET</p></div>",
