            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><p>WASHINGTON, Feb 18 (Reuters) - U.S. President Donald Trump will host a Board of Peace meeting on Thursday in Washington, where he will announce that member states have pledged more than $5 billion for reconstruction and humanitarian efforts in Gaza, the White House said.</p><p>\n              White House press secretary Karoline Leavitt told reporters that member states had committed to provide thousands of personnel for an international stabilization force for Gaza.</p><!-- Article --><p></p><p> (Reporting by Steve Holland, writing by Andrea Shalal; Editing by Doina Chiacu)</p></div>",
